acted in the eighteenth century to produce not only new kinds of knowledge but new kinds of families as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEnlightenmentzFrance. 0aFamilieszFrancexPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophersxFamily relationshipszFrance. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEnlightenment.  afamilies.  aphilosophy.  ascience.  aself-fashioning.  asentimentalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022638411540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226384252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226384252/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles